\remark{
\p{Precomposing squares gives the result of applying the functor
#{Hom(Q,-)} to the square. It is a well known result that this functor preserves
pullbacks. Likewise, postcomposition is given by #{Hom(-,Q)}, and this functor turns
pushouts in to pullbacks.
}
